    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-09T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="119"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3898: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-09T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 9, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. My telegram No. 78, March 6, 10 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d119fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> The Ethiopian Minister at Paris yesterday addressed a
                    communication to the Secretary General<note n="4" xml:id="d119fn4">For text of
                        Ethiopian reply, dated March 5, 1936, see League of Nations, <hi
                            rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, April 1936, p. 395.</note>
                    reiterating the Emperor’s acceptance of the [proposal of the?] Committee of
                    Thirteen and placing himself at the Committee’s disposal for any further
                    information desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
